1
00:01:26,169 --> 00:01:28,505
<i>Last week's sudden storm
is nothing new for the people...</i>

2
00:01:28,546 --> 00:01:30,215
Slow down, will ya?

3
00:01:30,340 --> 00:01:31,341
Relax, Rob.

4
00:01:31,383 --> 00:01:32,842
Easy for you to say.

5
00:01:32,884 --> 00:01:35,053
You don't have Amelia Lewis
waiting for you back home.

6
00:01:35,095 --> 00:01:38,223
Amelia Lewis, the Amelia Lewis?

7
00:01:38,390 --> 00:01:39,474
-The one with the...
-Yeah.

8
00:01:39,808 --> 00:01:43,853
Obviously we can't crash now.
We gotta get you back to Amelia Lewis.

9
00:01:44,396 --> 00:01:45,480
You're just jealous.

10
00:01:51,653 --> 00:01:53,738
-Did you hear that?<i>
-The Curse of Marguerite has been blamed...</i>

11
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:54,906
I think you broke something.

12
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:56,282
Then go check it out.

13
00:01:56,408 --> 00:01:57,951
I'm not going to check it out! You broke it.

14
00:01:58,743 --> 00:01:59,953
Go ahead in back, check it out.

15
00:02:00,412 --> 00:02:01,496
You know what we're hauling?

16
00:02:02,580 --> 00:02:03,707
You really think I'd let somebody put

17
00:02:03,790 --> 00:02:05,208
something on my truck,
I didn't know what it was?

18
00:02:05,250 --> 00:02:07,252
Do you know what's special about them?
You know what they are?

19
00:02:07,335 --> 00:02:09,713
Yeah, I heard the same thing, too.
I don't believe any of it.

20
00:02:09,754 --> 00:02:12,298
Pete said they shot them up with
a bunch of drugs and then they started...

21
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:14,175
Pete needs to learn to keep his mouth shut.

22
00:02:14,342 --> 00:02:15,677
<i>...of Marguerite's ghost.</i>

23
00:02:16,428 --> 00:02:17,429
Check it out!

24
00:02:19,180 --> 00:02:20,557
What? Are you scared?

25
00:02:21,182 --> 00:02:23,643
-I'm not scared.
-Amelia Lewis doesn't like scared boys.

26
00:02:23,768 --> 00:02:26,187
<i>Flood waters quickly receding
and meteorologists</i>

27
00:02:26,229 --> 00:02:28,648
<i>reporting a beautiful
weekend forecast, though.</i>

28
00:02:29,107 --> 00:02:30,483
Just watch the road, okay?

29
00:02:30,692 --> 00:02:34,738
If you're scared, just remember Amelia Lewis.

30
00:02:35,822 --> 00:02:38,742
-I gotta get back to Amelia Lewis.
-Shut up, okay?

31
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:59,179
What in the world? What the heck is that?

32
00:03:19,741 --> 00:03:21,242
Oh, man!

33
00:03:22,243 --> 00:03:23,787
You did break something!

34
00:03:26,206 --> 00:03:27,540
No.

35
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:31,336
What?

36
00:03:31,586 --> 00:03:33,546
You did break something.

37
00:03:34,923 --> 00:03:36,341
No! No!

38
00:03:37,717 --> 00:03:38,802
Rob?

39
00:03:43,723 --> 00:03:44,808
Rob?

40
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:07,497
It's started.

41
00:04:09,708 --> 00:04:11,126
It's started.

42
00:04:19,926 --> 00:04:21,678
No! No! No!

43
00:04:23,888 --> 00:04:27,434
No! No! No! No!

44
00:04:27,726 --> 00:04:29,519
Stay away from me! No! No!

45
00:04:30,353 --> 00:04:32,522
No! No! No!

46
00:04:54,711 --> 00:04:58,298
I now pronounce you man and wife.
You may kiss the bride.

47
00:05:01,926 --> 00:05:03,094
Yeah!

48
00:05:03,386 --> 00:05:07,182
Ladies and gentlemen,
I present to you Mr. and Mrs. Hamilton.

49
00:05:11,061 --> 00:05:12,437
Yeah!

50
00:05:24,741 --> 00:05:25,992
Come on.

51
00:05:29,037 --> 00:05:30,538
Cheers!

52
00:05:35,877 --> 00:05:39,047
-Hi, how are you?
-Good. Wasn't it beautiful?

53
00:05:39,089 --> 00:05:42,050
It was beautiful.
I mean, it's been a long time coming, huh?

54
00:05:42,092 --> 00:05:44,260
-Those guys are great.
-They're great together.

55
00:06:01,111 --> 00:06:03,863
Oh, my God! So happy for you.

56
00:06:03,905 --> 00:06:06,825
It was so beautiful. Let me see. Let me see.

57
00:06:07,867 --> 00:06:11,579
I'm so happy for you guys. It was amazing.

58
00:06:18,753 --> 00:06:20,505
I'll be right back. So happy for you.

59
00:06:25,385 --> 00:06:26,970
-Hello, darling.
-Hi.

60
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:56,291
You didn't have to come to her wedding.

61
00:06:56,791 --> 00:06:59,044
You kidding me? This is great.

62
00:06:59,669 --> 00:07:01,796
Let's get away for the day.

63
00:07:03,131 --> 00:07:05,175
I got plans this weekend.

64
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:10,055
I was gonna hole myself up in my room
and listen to Lionel Richie and cry.

65
00:07:10,930 --> 00:07:11,973
Come on.

66
00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:17,228
Remember when we were kids and our folks
would always take us and Bryce out...

67
00:07:17,812 --> 00:07:20,523
Chris, I'm so sorry. I'm such an idiot.

68
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:24,527
When's the last time we were out
at the point together?

69
00:07:24,569 --> 00:07:26,446
I haven't been there in a long time, Ash.

70
00:07:26,529 --> 00:07:30,241
Place doesn't exactly conjure up
good feelings for me.

71
00:07:30,325 --> 00:07:32,994
Yeah, but, I mean, we should go.

72
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:36,289
I go out all the time,
and Ian's got his family boat for the day.

73
00:07:36,373 --> 00:07:39,626
I don't want to hang out with Ian.
He hates me.

74
00:07:39,709 --> 00:07:42,128
Please! Come on, Chris.

75
00:07:42,212 --> 00:07:45,215
Sam's going, of course. Kerri will be there.

76
00:07:45,256 --> 00:07:47,550
-You trying to set me up right now?
-It's not a set-up.

77
00:07:47,634 --> 00:07:48,843
I don't need a pity date, Ash.

78
00:07:48,885 --> 00:07:51,012
It's not, you'd be doing me a favor.

79
00:07:51,429 --> 00:07:54,557
Ian always gets so plastered
every time we go out on the boat.

80
00:07:54,641 --> 00:07:57,894
If you guys don't come, he's just gonna
want to mess around the whole time.

81
00:07:58,019 --> 00:08:01,523
And I want somebody who can
actually carry a conversation, you know?

82
00:08:02,023 --> 00:08:03,400
You got problems in paradise?

83
00:08:04,275 --> 00:08:08,571
No, just Ian's Ian.

84
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:10,865
You know how it is.

85
00:08:10,907 --> 00:08:13,952
Frat parties were fun at first,
but, I mean, you gotta grow up sometime.

86
00:08:16,121 --> 00:08:19,332
Please, please, please, please.
You have to come.

87
00:08:22,377 --> 00:08:23,545
All right.

88
00:08:23,628 --> 00:08:25,255
Okay, you will not regret this.

89
00:08:25,422 --> 00:08:27,799
-I regret it already.
-I'm so excited.

90
00:08:27,882 --> 00:08:31,386
Can you slow down, please?
I'm trying to be somber here.

91
00:08:34,222 --> 00:08:36,516
Please tell me some good news.

92
00:08:37,892 --> 00:08:41,396
So tell me, Hutch, those tech guys
that called this in, were they right?

93
00:08:41,479 --> 00:08:42,647
Looks like it.

94
00:08:42,731 --> 00:08:44,983
On a scale of one to ten,
one being, "Let's go get some coffee."

95
00:08:45,066 --> 00:08:46,234
Ten being,

96
00:08:46,317 --> 00:08:49,195
"How do you want to spend your last night
on earth," what are we looking at?

97
00:08:49,237 --> 00:08:51,906
Ten? Looks more like a 20.

98
00:08:52,073 --> 00:08:53,283
That's what I was afraid of.

99
00:08:53,867 --> 00:08:55,827
"Specimen 0," what's that?

100
00:08:56,244 --> 00:09:00,331
I don't know, but whatever it was,
it was a lot bigger than the others.

101
00:09:07,339 --> 00:09:09,382
You shouldn't be out here!

102
00:09:10,884 --> 00:09:14,220
Unless you prepared for what you might find!

103
00:09:14,721 --> 00:09:16,473
Better get back, sir! It's not safe just yet!

104
00:09:19,309 --> 00:09:20,310
No! No!

105
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:25,899
The danger just getting started!

106
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:33,239
It's gonna be
one of those backwater towns, huh?

107
00:09:33,281 --> 00:09:36,242
Salvage what you can.
I want an expanding perimeter on the swamp.

108
00:09:36,326 --> 00:09:37,702
Yes, sir!

109
00:09:44,376 --> 00:09:47,128
Hey, Chris, it's me.

110
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:52,967
Why don't you give me a call?
I'm just thinking about you.

111
00:09:57,764 --> 00:10:00,975
I told her, "Look, honey, Trevor is my man."

112
00:10:01,059 --> 00:10:02,102
Yes, I did.

113
00:10:02,185 --> 00:10:05,230
I told her that she lost her chances with him
that last night at bingo,

114
00:10:05,313 --> 00:10:07,065
and that if she didn't like it, well,

115
00:10:07,107 --> 00:10:11,319
then I'd be happy to walk on over there
and shove my foot right up...

116
00:10:11,403 --> 00:10:12,404
Morning, Marge.

117
00:10:17,075 --> 00:10:20,328
Marge! Marge!

118
00:10:20,912 --> 00:10:23,415
Will you get that damn hearing aid fixed?

119
00:10:24,833 --> 00:10:27,002
-Lucille.
-Ranger Hardin.

120
00:10:27,043 --> 00:10:29,629
You know, that Davids boy was out
past my property the other night

121
00:10:29,713 --> 00:10:31,047
blasting his dynamite again.

122
00:10:31,089 --> 00:10:33,299
Yeah, well,
I'll go have a little talk with him, then.

123
00:10:33,383 --> 00:10:36,553
Well, you best head on down to the dock,
then, 'cause he's there right now.

124
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:38,722
And I hear Chris is with him.

125
00:10:39,389 --> 00:10:40,390
My Chris?

126
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:51,276
This is Specimen number five.

127
00:10:51,901 --> 00:10:55,071
-Is that the last one?
-No, I got a few more to collect.

128
00:10:59,993 --> 00:11:02,037
-Do you hear that?
-Yeah.

129
00:11:02,704 --> 00:11:05,707
-We should go check that out.
-All right, come on.

130
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:33,568
-Did you hear that?
-I did.

131
00:11:33,902 --> 00:11:36,071
-It's over there.
-Let's go.

132
00:11:52,420 --> 00:11:54,297
All right, let's do this.

133
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:55,715
I'm excited, and you?

134
00:11:55,965 --> 00:11:58,301
-Yeah, I know.
-You know I am excited.

135
00:11:58,385 --> 00:12:01,221
I know, Chris, Chris, Chris,
that's all you talk about.

136
00:12:01,304 --> 00:12:04,432
Yeah, well, we haven't done this in so long.

137
00:12:12,065 --> 00:12:14,275
Just hang back with the boat,
I gotta go find Chris.

138
00:12:14,359 --> 00:12:15,568
Yes, ma'am.

139
00:12:17,737 --> 00:12:21,074
Hey, partner, there's some good-lookers
down in the swamp today, eh?

140
00:12:22,409 --> 00:12:23,785
Drop dead.

141
00:12:25,829 --> 00:12:27,914
Make me wish I was 20 year younger.

142
00:12:27,997 --> 00:12:29,916
Oglin' the coeds again, boys?

143
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:33,962
Sorry, Ranger Hardin.
Just enjoying the Blackbriar sights.

144
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:40,343
Hey, Chris, you made it!

145
00:12:40,385 --> 00:12:41,594
Hi!

146
00:12:42,554 --> 00:12:43,722
Chris.

147
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:47,058
Hey. Fun.

148
00:12:47,142 --> 00:12:48,560
Don't worry about him, you're here with me.

149
00:12:48,727 --> 00:12:52,647
Hey, Ashley! How are you? Good to see you.
Chris, what's up?

150
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:54,399
Right this way, dear wench.

151
00:12:54,649 --> 00:12:56,234
-Shut up.
-What?

152
00:12:56,317 --> 00:12:58,737
Hey, Chris, like my new swimsuit?

153
00:13:00,238 --> 00:13:02,115
It's cute, thank you.

154
00:13:03,575 --> 00:13:05,910
You need help with the beer
or anything like that?

155
00:13:06,411 --> 00:13:07,662
Come on, let's go.

156
00:13:07,996 --> 00:13:09,831
You chuckin' your line today, Brutus?

157
00:13:10,081 --> 00:13:12,375
Sure. You want us to bring you back a big,
old gator head?

158
00:13:12,417 --> 00:13:13,710
You can hang it on your wall?

159
00:13:15,587 --> 00:13:18,381
You get brave on us, Sheriff,
come out on gator water with us, huh?

160
00:13:20,050 --> 00:13:22,052
Chipmunk said
you should come out to the boat with us.

161
00:13:22,135 --> 00:13:24,054
Well, maybe sometime I'll surprise you,

162
00:13:24,137 --> 00:13:27,766
but in the meantime,
be careful and watch the drinking, huh?

163
00:13:28,641 --> 00:13:29,851
Yeah, don't be so scared.

164
00:13:31,811 --> 00:13:34,564
So you actually went to that wedding.
What a loser.

165
00:13:35,398 --> 00:13:36,399
-Sucker.
-Stop it.

166
00:13:36,483 --> 00:13:37,650
It was a sweet gesture.

167
00:13:37,734 --> 00:13:40,028
A true gentleman can admit
when he's been defeated.

168
00:13:40,070 --> 00:13:43,073
Yeah, but what loser
wants to be a gentleman?

169
00:13:43,239 --> 00:13:45,408
Stop it. Stop.

170
00:13:46,993 --> 00:13:48,995
If this is going on all weekend,
I'll shoot somebody.

171
00:13:52,999 --> 00:13:54,084
Hey, Ranger Hardin.

172
00:13:56,211 --> 00:13:57,420
Hey, Ashley.

173
00:13:57,712 --> 00:13:59,923
Mom. I'll be right back.

174
00:14:00,632 --> 00:14:02,008
Just wait up.

175
00:14:03,885 --> 00:14:05,178
Mom, what are you doing here?

176
00:14:05,220 --> 00:14:07,305
I have been calling your cell phone for days!

177
00:14:07,389 --> 00:14:09,432
I've been busy, Mom. I'm sorry, okay?

178
00:14:09,516 --> 00:14:11,726
So, how was the wedding?

179
00:14:11,810 --> 00:14:13,478
I mean, I thought maybe
you'd want to talk afterwards.

180
00:14:13,561 --> 00:14:17,232
It was fine. Whatever, I don't care.
It was nice.

181
00:14:20,777 --> 00:14:22,195
Is that the Davids' boat?

182
00:14:22,445 --> 00:14:23,488
Yes.

183
00:14:24,614 --> 00:14:28,076
My office has gotten a few calls
about Ian doing some dynamite fishing.

184
00:14:28,159 --> 00:14:29,327
Now, I haven't caught him yet,

185
00:14:29,411 --> 00:14:32,580
but if I do catch him and whoever he's with,
they're gonna be in some big trouble,

186
00:14:32,664 --> 00:14:35,041
so I'm hoping that is not what
you were planning on doing this weekend.

187
00:14:35,083 --> 00:14:36,668
No, we're just going out
to have some fun, all right?

188
00:14:36,710 --> 00:14:38,128
It's not a big deal, it's innocent, okay?

189
00:14:38,378 --> 00:14:40,880
Okay, you just be careful.

190
00:14:41,381 --> 00:14:45,010
That swamp, it can be mean.

191
00:14:47,929 --> 00:14:50,557
Dad told me that you filed the other day.

192
00:14:53,101 --> 00:14:55,228
I thought you were
gonna try to patch things up.

193
00:14:55,854 --> 00:14:57,397
Honey, it's not that simple.

194
00:14:57,897 --> 00:15:01,317
And are you sure that this is
the right move for you guys?

195
00:15:01,901 --> 00:15:04,320
-Christopher, honey.
-It's fine. It's fine.

196
00:15:09,534 --> 00:15:11,453
Kerri Ponter, is that you?

197
00:15:12,370 --> 00:15:13,371
Yes, ma'am.

198
00:15:13,705 --> 00:15:16,499
-Does your grandma know you're here?
-Mom.

199
00:15:18,335 --> 00:15:19,586
-Are you nuts?
-What?

200
00:15:19,669 --> 00:15:21,713
She's underage for drinking
and you're dragging her out

201
00:15:21,755 --> 00:15:23,006
-to your wild orgy.
-She's not drinking.

202
00:15:23,048 --> 00:15:24,382
Wild orgies, what are you talking about?

203
00:15:24,424 --> 00:15:25,675
Where do you get this stuff from?

204
00:15:25,717 --> 00:15:28,219
-Do you think she'll call my grandma?
-No.

205
00:15:29,262 --> 00:15:31,473
We're just going out on the boat
to have a little fun on the water.

206
00:15:31,556 --> 00:15:33,725
Man, come on. You coming? I'm shoving off.

207
00:15:33,808 --> 00:15:35,352
-All right, I gotta go.
-Wait, wait.

208
00:15:35,393 --> 00:15:37,145
-I gotta go.
-Wait, wait, wait, listen...

209
00:15:38,646 --> 00:15:42,859
Honey, I really want to hang out with you, so,

210
00:15:43,985 --> 00:15:46,696
how about I make you some dinner,
something like that?

211
00:15:46,905 --> 00:15:49,449
Maybe. Yeah, no, that'd be nice. I'd like that.

212
00:15:49,532 --> 00:15:51,284
-Let's do it. I'll talk to you.
-Okay.

213
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:52,994
Be safe.

214
00:16:02,587 --> 00:16:04,214
<i>Au revoir,</i> Ranger!

215
00:16:08,134 --> 00:16:09,594
Be careful out there.

216
00:16:10,845 --> 00:16:12,222
I like her!

217
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:31,741
Can't stop us now, we're going!

218
00:16:34,619 --> 00:16:35,912
We're going over this way.

219
00:16:41,418 --> 00:16:43,878
Let's head back to the station.

220
00:16:43,962 --> 00:16:45,422
Yes, ma'am.

221
00:17:11,656 --> 00:17:17,078
I tried to hold you off, but you keep pushing.

222
00:17:21,458 --> 00:17:25,045
These people,
they ain't the ones hurting you.

223
00:17:26,254 --> 00:17:27,255
No!

224
00:17:28,715 --> 00:17:31,343
Haven't you been in pain long enough?

225
00:17:33,678 --> 00:17:35,013
Let it go.

226
00:17:38,308 --> 00:17:42,145
What's it gonna take for you to be satisfied?

227
00:17:56,326 --> 00:17:58,161
It's war, then.

228
00:18:01,664 --> 00:18:03,917
Keep going, it's right up there.

229
00:19:04,269 --> 00:19:05,562
Who got it better than us, Brutus?

230
00:19:09,024 --> 00:19:12,235
Every day a good day in the swamp.
Even bad day a good day in the swamp.

231
00:19:12,569 --> 00:19:15,321
You got that right, my friend. That's all true.

232
00:19:17,574 --> 00:19:19,242
How much further
until we get to that other line?

233
00:19:20,076 --> 00:19:21,077
We should be there by now.

234
00:19:21,161 --> 00:19:22,996
Hush, hush, looky there.

235
00:19:23,747 --> 00:19:24,956
Looky there.

236
00:19:25,415 --> 00:19:26,833
That's a big, old gator track there.

237
00:19:27,042 --> 00:19:29,294
Yeah, yeah, I think we coming up
on something big, man.

238
00:19:29,753 --> 00:19:32,255
We got him on the run, too,
the way that line is all tight.

239
00:19:35,383 --> 00:19:37,427
Come on, let's get in there and get him.

240
00:19:45,060 --> 00:19:47,145
-Y'all want fish for dinner?
-We don't have any poles, though.

241
00:19:50,023 --> 00:19:52,192
-Oh, my God!
-Here you go. Here you go.

242
00:19:59,324 --> 00:20:00,492
Yeah, baby.

243
00:20:02,118 --> 00:20:05,622
Everybody, lunch is almost ready! Lunch!

244
00:20:05,747 --> 00:20:06,748
Y'all want to fish first?

245
00:20:06,790 --> 00:20:08,917
